{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"body":"Plan-review PASS feedback disposition and remediation:\n- Accepted: defined pin/phase wire formats, execution compatibility, prerequisite result schema, STATUS-history derivation, single-snapshot inbound-block discovery, rollback behavior, fidelity pass/fail contract, atomic ACs, and the attest.py sibling ordering edge.\n- Accepted title feedback: renamed the epic to cover relationship validity, execution reviews, close enforcement, and prerequisite consistency.\n- Kept approved decisions: 0.80 remains an operator-set v1 risk policy rather than a calibration spike/config surface; prerequisite batching remains the target architecture but cannot ship unless it matches the one-per-call gold baseline, otherwise it falls back to smaller/individual calls.\n- Declined low-validity suggestions for an in-toto link payload and a new separate ADR: pins are additive fields in the existing signed plan-review manifest and the advanced gate documentation is the approved architectural record.\nThe material edits invalidate the first PASS signature; rerunning review before continuing."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1784518549011874001,"uuid":"f2cb2db9-d12b-4237-89bb-2307ad20d1c8"}